    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-07T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-07T16:00:00-05:00" n="47"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.85/837: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-07T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 7, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>616. Department’s A–600, April 2, regarding Italian tankers. In drafting the
                    proposed alterations, I request that the following points be considered with
                    reference to the objections raised in the War Shipping Administration’s letter
                    of February 25 enclosed with the Department’s instruction No. 1107 of March
                        15:<note n="91" xml:id="d47fn91">Not printed.</note>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Paragraph third. Full information regarding the privileged debts
                            referred to in this paragraph was sent to the Department with this
                            Embassy’s despatch No. 1529 of January 30.<note n="91" xml:id="d47fn92"
                                >Not printed.</note> For us now to demand from the Federation
                            photostatic copies of the documents disputed [<hi rend="italic"
                                >disputing</hi>] the nature and amount of these debts would in my
                            opinion be resented, and I am strongly of the opinion that no such
                            request should be made since it could give the impression that we
                            doubted the Federation’s good faith.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Paragraph fourth. I trust that it will be possible to accept the
                            provision in the draft requiring payment to the Federation within 5 days
                            following the signature of the contract. The Department will recall that
                            the original draft required that payment be made in New York on the date
                            the contract was signed and that no objection was then raised by the
                            administration.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Please telegraph the English text of the desired alterations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
